CPPLs followers analysis

rr #Number of followers by CCPL (comparison) options(scipen=10000) canpoli.tmls.filtered %>% group_by(name) %>% summarize(avgfollowers = median(followers_count)) %>% arrange(desc(avgfollowers)) %>% ggplot(., aes(x = name, y=avgfollowers, fill=avgfollowers)) + geom_bar(stat=identity)+ theme(legend.title = element_blank())+ ggplot2::labs( x = NULL, y = NULL, title = of followers of CPPLs, subtitle = follower counts: February 18 - March 29 ```

rr #All leaders excluding Justin Trudeau since Trudeau seems to be an outlier canpoli.tmls.filtered %>% filter(name != Trudeau) %>% group_by(name) %>% summarize(avgfollowers = median(followers_count)) %>% arrange(desc(avgfollowers)) %>% ggplot(., aes(x = name, y=avgfollowers, fill =avgfollowers)) + geom_bar(stat=identity)+ theme(legend.title = element_blank())+ ggplot2::labs( x = NULL, y = NULL, title = of followers of CPPLs (excl. Trudeau), subtitle = follower counts: February 18 - March 29 ```

Tweets favourited analysis

rr #Number of tweets favourited by party leader (comparison) #Count of tweets favourited ggplot(canpoli.tmls.filtered, aes(x = name, y=favorite_count, fill=favorite_count)) + geom_bar(stat=identity) + theme(legend.title = element_blank())+ #theme_classic()+ #facet_wrap(~ source)+ ggplot2::labs( x = NULL, y = NULL, title = of CPPLs tweets favourited, subtitle = counts: February 18 - March 29 ```

rr #Average of tweets favourited canpoli.tmls.filtered %>% group_by(name) %>%
summarise(Number_of_Tweets = n_distinct(status_id), Number_of_Likes = sum(favorite_count)) %>% mutate(Avg_Likes=Number_of_Likes/Number_of_Tweets)%>% ggplot(., aes(x = name, y=Avg_Likes, fill =Avg_Likes)) + geom_bar(stat=identity)+ theme(legend.title = element_blank())+ ggplot2::labs( x = NULL, y = NULL, title = number favourites per CPPL tweet, subtitle = counts: February 18 - March 29 ```

Tweet hashtag analysis (CPPL)

rr #Hashtags by party leader (comparison) #Create a seperate chart for each party leader to examine main themes #Hastags by all CPPL (top 10) canpoli.tmls.filtered %>% select(name, hashtags, is_retweet) %>% filter(is_retweet ==FALSE) %>% mutate(tolower(hashtags)) %>% unnest_tokens(word, hashtags) %>% count(name,word, sort = TRUE) %>% filter(!is.na(word), n>1) %>% ungroup() %>% arrange(desc(n)) %>% top_n(10) %>% ggplot(., aes(x = reorder(word, -n),y=n, fill=n)) + geom_bar(stat=identity)+ theme(legend.title = element_blank())+ coord_flip()+ ggplot2::labs( x = NULL, y = NULL, title = 10 hashtags used by all CPPL, subtitle = counts: February 18 - March 29
